cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with distributed computing and parallelization techniques. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses coded MapReduce techniques which involve coding theory. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses inter-node communication costs and proposes a novel D2D coded caching algorithm. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with optimizing the performance of a distributed computing system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the assignment of computational tasks to nodes and the preprocessing of subtasks.
